# Core Model Definitions

## S5LA — Semantic 5-Layer Architecture

| Layer | Name | Processor | Defensive Access |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| L1 | Semantic Category | Human | ✅ Full |
| L2 | Semantic Layer | Human | ✅ Full |
| L3 | Semantic Object | Human | ✅ Full |
| L4 | Semantic Pattern | AI (implicit) | ⚠️ Indirect only |
| L5 | Semantic Atom | AI (invisible) | ❌ None currently |

Read bottom-up. L5 is foundation; L1 is top-level classification.

## SIF — Semantic Integrity Framework

```text
L1 — Semantic Decision    (apex)    judgment criteria & conflict resolution
         ↑
L2 — Semantic Structure   (middle)  information weight & priority hierarchy
         ↑
L3 — Semantic Architecture (base)   identity, authority, prohibition
```

**Build order: L3 → L2 → L1. Never top-down.**

## Defensive Boundary

- SIF defends **L1–L3 only**.
- L4/L5 are explicitly undefended. Do not claim otherwise.
- Compensating controls for L4/L5: sandboxing, capability restriction, output monitoring.

## Diagnostic Gating Logic

```text
L3 gate → any ★★★ ❌? STOP. Full L3 redesign required.
L2 gate → any ★★★ ❌? L2 restructure. L1 findings are provisional.
L1 gate → any ★★★ ❌? Targeted amendment.
All ✅  → PASS (within SIF scope — L4/L5 residual risk remains)
```

## Three Contexts of Semantic Corruption

| Context | Where | Primary Risk |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Input | User input, external data | Injection, contamination |
| Reasoning | Internal LLM interpretation | Priority drift, semantic mixing |
| Output | Final response, actions | Misaligned or malformed output |

## Human-in-the-Point Criteria

A decision requires human judgment when **any** of these are true:

1. Action is irreversible
2. Action affects parties outside the system scope
3. Normative judgment required (not capturable in constraints)
4. AI confidence cannot be independently verified
